This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of neural networks for machine translation is a popular research area in NLP, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The comparison of performance between different machine translation systems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the translation of different language varieties, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CY).
